# Social Analytics

Guidelines for measuring social media performance, building reports, conducting A/B tests, and translating data into strategic decisions.

## Metrics Hierarchy

Not all metrics are created equal. Organize them by business relevance:

| Tier | Metric Category | Key Metrics | Why It Matters |
|------|---------------|------------|---------------|
| Tier 1: Business Impact | Revenue and conversions | Social-attributed revenue, cost per acquisition, lead volume | Directly proves ROI of social investment |
| Tier 2: Behavioral | Traffic and actions | Link clicks, landing page visits, email signups, app installs | Shows audience moving from social to business outcomes |
| Tier 3: Engagement | Interaction quality | Engagement rate, save rate, share rate, comment depth | Indicates content resonance and community health |
| Tier 4: Awareness | Reach and exposure | Impressions, reach, video views, follower growth | Shows brand visibility and audience expansion |

