## A/B Testing Protocol

| Test Element | Variables | Sample Size | Duration | Success Metric |
|-------------|-----------|-------------|----------|---------------|
| Post timing | 2-3 different publish times | 10+ posts per time slot | 3-4 weeks | Average engagement rate by time |
| Hook style | 2 hook approaches on same topic | 5+ posts per approach | 2-3 weeks | First-3-second retention or engagement rate |
| Format | Carousel vs. single vs. video on same topic | 5+ posts per format | 3-4 weeks | Reach and engagement rate |
| Caption length | Short (< 50 words) vs. long (200+ words) | 10+ posts per length | 4 weeks | Engagement rate and saves |
| CTA phrasing | Different CTAs on similar content | 10+ posts per CTA | 4 weeks | Action completion rate |
| Hashtag sets | 3 different hashtag groups | 10+ posts per set | 4 weeks | Reach from hashtags |
| Thumbnail / first slide | 2-3 visual variations | 3+ per variation | 2 weeks | Click-through rate |

### Testing Discipline

```text
A/B Testing Rules
├── Test one variable at a time
│   └── Changing multiple variables makes results uninterpretable
├── Define success metric before launching
│   └── Choosing the metric after seeing results introduces bias
├── Set minimum sample size before starting
│   └── Do not call a winner after 3 posts
├── Run tests for sufficient duration
│   └── At least 2 full weeks to account for day-of-week variance
├── Document every test and result
│   └── Build institutional knowledge; avoid re-running the same tests
└── Act on results
    └── A test that does not change strategy is a wasted test
```

